    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. one thing i keep hearing is that including these lessons is basically just \"science-based\" and \"inclusive,\" while the people who don't want them are just being \"intolerant\" or \"outdated.\" is there any actual truth to that, or is that just how people are framing it to win the argument?",
